    <body>
      <head>Hallmut Hatschek</head>
      <div>

        <p>Son of <ref cRef="entity-000339">Oskar Hatschek</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-003244">Klara
            Hatschek (<hi rend="italic">née</hi> Schiff)</ref>. Hellmut, who had been studying law,
          died in a climbing accident. His death notice recorded: <cit>
            <q>We announce the death of our only child / <hi rend="bold">Helmut Hatschek,</hi> /
              candidate for law / who, on Sunday in the mountains, which he loved above all else,
              fell victim to a fatal accident. / The mortal frame of our dear departed will be
              cremated on Wednesday the 12th of this month at 3 p.m. in the Brux Crematorium. /
              AUSSIG, October 11, 1932. / Editor-in-Chief Oskar Hatschek and wife.</q>
          </cit>
        </p>

        <p>As a result of his death, his mother descended slowly into insanity, dying in 1939.</p>
      </div>
